        <mxCell id="p4_n19" value="&lt;div style=&quot;font-family:Consolas,Arial;color:#263238;font-size:10px;line-height:1.35&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;background-color:#F2E9FF;color:#5B3B72;font-family:Arial;font-size:13px;padding:5px&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;v_simulation_shortfalls&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;font-size:9px&quot;&gt;VIEW / PROJECTION&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;padding:7px;text-align:left&quot;&gt;simulation_id uuid&lt;br&gt;material_id uuid&lt;br&gt;required / allocated / shortfall numeric(20,4)&lt;br&gt;project + PO + priority context&lt;br&gt;export source for missing-material document&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;overflow=hidden;shadow=0;fillColor=#F2F2F2;strokeColor=#9E9E9E;strokeWidth=1.4;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=0;" vertex="1" parent="1" dataKind="view" dataName="v_simulation_shortfalls">
          <mxGeometry x="2060" y="1321" width="420" height="151" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p4_n20" value="&lt;div style=&quot;font-family:Consolas,Arial;color:#263238;font-size:10px;line-height:1.35&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;background-color:#F2E9FF;color:#5B3B72;font-family:Arial;font-size:13px;padding:5px&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;v_launch_readiness&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;font-size:9px&quot;&gt;VIEW / PROJECTION&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;padding:7px;text-align:left&quot;&gt;launch_operation_id uuid&lt;br&gt;policy/BOM/PO snapshot references&lt;br&gt;meeting_minutes_present boolean&lt;br&gt;approved boolean&lt;br&gt;ready_to_finalize boolean&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;overflow=hidden;shadow=0;fillColor=#F2F2F2;strokeColor=#9E9E9E;strokeWidth=1.4;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=0;" vertex="1" parent="1" dataKind="view" dataName="v_launch_readiness">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="1629" width="420" height="151" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p4_note0" value="&lt;div style=&quot;font-family:Arial;color:#5F4B00;font-size:13px;line-height:1.35&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Full-snapshot BOM&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11px&quot;&gt;Each accepted xlsx upload creates one project-level bom_revisions row and the complete set of bom_revision_items for all FGPN/material components. No valid-from/valid-to component deltas are used. Exactly one active revision per project is enforced by a partial unique index; replacing it never deletes the old snapshot.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;overflow=hidden;shadow=0;fillColor=#FFF9D9;strokeColor=#D6B656;strokeWidth=1.4;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=0;dashed=1;spacing=10;" vertex="1" parent="1" dataKind="note" dataName="Full-snapshot BOM">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="1850" width="1215" height="127" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p4_note1" value="&lt;div style=&quot;font-family:Arial;color:#5F4B00;font-size:13px;line-height:1.35&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Reproducible simulation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11px&quot;&gt;Each PO item snapshots requested, already launched, and already in-manufacturing quantities. Each material snapshots warehouse, WIP, transit, planned, policy-usable totals, and the pool breakdown. Every selected future arrival is a separate immutable row with quantity/date. Together with exact PO/BOM/policy versions, the same input hash reproduces the result.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;overflow=hidden;shadow=0;fillColor=#FFF9D9;strokeColor=#D6B656;strokeWidth=1.4;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=0;dashed=1;spacing=10;" vertex="1" parent="1" dataKind="note" dataName="Reproducible simulation">
          <mxGeometry x="1345" y="1850" width="1215" height="127" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p4_note2" value="&lt;div style=&quot;font-family:Arial;color:#5F4B00;font-size:13px;line-height:1.35&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Meeting-minutes gate&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11px&quot;&gt;A deferred trigger blocks finalized launch_operations unless meeting_minutes_document_id is a valid stored PDF and approval exists. Warehouse instructions additionally require a finalized/approved operation. Future-stock simulations never post inventory; their clearly marked draft document is retained.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;overflow=hidden;shadow=0;fillColor=#FFF9D9;strokeColor=#D6B656;strokeWidth=1.4;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=0;dashed=1;spacing=10;" vertex="1" parent="1" dataKind="note" dataName="Meeting-minutes gate">
